  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bbf \u0b9a\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc7 \u0b85\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bae\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1 \u0ba4\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bca\u0baf\u0bcd\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u2013 \u0ba4\u0bca\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b92\u0bb4\u0bc1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b86\u0ba3\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rumors of permission for voice services from tomorrow morning are false \u2013 Telecom Regulatory Commission",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Sri Lanka Telecommunication Regulatory Commission Chairman Jayantha De Silva has said that a letter circulating on social media requesting internet service providers to allow only voice communications from tomorrow morning is fake.",
        "He said that no such restrictions or other shutdowns are planned",
        "Meanwhile, reports have surfaced that the President has ordered to allow only voice communications to ensure national security.",
        "Based on the information provided by the National Intelligence Service, the Minister of Defense and Technology, President Gotabaya Rajapaksa, has informed the Secretary of the Ministry of Technology that demonstrations are planned in several areas of Colombo on Saturday 9th, especially in the vicinity of Gallimugatidal.",
        "He also said in his letter that the gang is trying to cause damage to lives and property.",
        "Demonstrators have in the past used social media and telecommunication networks to escalate the situation and spread misinformation.",
        "Due to this, the Minister of Defense and the Minister of Technical Affairs have ordered the President to ensure that only voice communications are allowed from six o'clock tomorrow morning until further notice."
      ],
